  "prompt": "Where can I get Marvel comics free?",
  "response": "While obtaining copyrighted materials for free without permission is generally illegal, there are legitimate ways to access Marvel comics without paying. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Marvel's Official Website and App**: Marvel sometimes offers free previews and full issues on their website or through their official app, Marvel Unlimited.\n2. **Public Libraries**: Many libraries have digital and physical collections of Marvel comics that you can borrow.\n3. **ComiXology**: This digital comic platform occasionally offers free issues and promotions.\n4. **Free Comic Book Day**: This annual event involves comic book shops giving away free comics, including Marvel titles.\n5. **Marvel's YouTube Channel**: Marvel occasionally posts motion comic versions of some of their stories, which can be viewed for free.\n6. **Publisher Promotions and Events**: Keep an eye out for promotional events or giveaways hosted by Marvel or comic book stores.\n\nAlways ensure you're accessing content through legal and legitimate channels.",
